commitResults.messageTitle: Update the appendix: requirements section of the developer guide
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's update the sections in the the appendix: requirements section,
so that the details of the project are captured accurately. The
sections specifically are: the Target user profile, value proposition,
User Stories, Use cases, Non-functional requirements, Glossary.
Let's populate the user guide with info relevant to our project.

Add context to commands passed to parser
commitResults.messageBody:
The parser needs to know which tab the user is currently on so that
it can execute the command with the right handler.

Let's add a new method in MainWindow.java that retrieves the current tab
the user is on, and modify the argument sent to parser by prepending
the tab name to the command entered by user.
